{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/38703", "id": 99758520, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0OTk3NTg1MjA=", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/38703", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/38703.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/38703.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/38703", "number": 38703, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "rustbuild: implement precise LLVM stamping", "user": {"login": "xen0n", "id": 1175567, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjExNzU1Njc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1175567?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/xen0n", "html_url": "https://github.com/xen0n", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xen0n/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xen0n/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xen0n/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xen0n/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xen0n/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xen0n/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xen0n/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xen0n/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/xen0n/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "This PR implements precise stamping for LLVM builds. By introducing a mirror struct between the build step and `cmake::Config`, we're able to serialize and compare the build configuration, while retaining the same behavior towards CMake.\r\n\r\n## New stamp format\r\n\r\nThe new LLVM build stamp looks like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n# If this file is modified, then llvm will be forcibly cleaned and then rebuilt.\r\n# The actual contents of this file do not matter, but to trigger a change on the\r\n# build bots then the contents should be changed so git updates the mtime.\r\n2016-12-19\r\n\r\ntarget: mips64el-unknown-linux-gnuabi64\r\nhost: mips64el-unknown-linux-gnuabi64\r\nprofile: Release\r\ndefine: \"CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER\" = \"ccache\"\r\ndefine: \"CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER_ARG1\" = \"c++\"\r\ndefine: \"CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS\" = \"-ffunction-sections -fdata-sections -fPIC\"\r\ndefine: \"CMAKE_C_COMPILER\" = \"ccache\"\r\ndefine: \"CMAKE_C_COMPILER_ARG1\" = \"cc\"\r\ndefine: \"CMAKE_C_FLAGS\" = \"-ffunction-sections -fdata-sections -fPIC\"\r\ndefine: \"LLVM_DEFAULT_TARGET_TRIPLE\" = \"mips64el-unknown-linux-gnuabi64\"\r\ndefine: \"LLVM_ENABLE_ASSERTIONS\" = \"OFF\"\r\ndefine: \"LLVM_ENABLE_LIBEDIT\" = \"OFF\"\r\ndefine: \"LLVM_ENABLE_TERMINFO\" = \"OFF\"\r\ndefine: \"LLVM_ENABLE_ZLIB\" = \"OFF\"\r\ndefine: \"LLVM_INCLUDE_DOCS\" = \"OFF\"\r\ndefine: \"LLVM_INCLUDE_EXAMPLES\" = \"OFF\"\r\ndefine: \"LLVM_INCLUDE_TESTS\" = \"OFF\"\r\ndefine: \"LLVM_PARALLEL_COMPILE_JOBS\" = \"4\"\r\ndefine: \"LLVM_TARGETS_TO_BUILD\" = \"Mips\"\r\ndefine: \"LLVM_TARGET_ARCH\" = \"mips64el\"\r\ndefine: \"WITH_POLLY\" = \"OFF\"\r\nbuild_arg: \"-j\"\r\nbuild_arg: \"4\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nApart from the original clean trigger, there's now complete CMake configuration. The build was done on a MIPS64 box, hence the exotic triples. Also notice the fact that only the `Mips` backend is enabled is reflected in the stamp, so do other configuration; if any of these is touched, a rebuild would be correctly triggered.\r\n\r\nOne may argue that it's some real complexity brought in with little benefit; the fact is people do make silly moves sometimes, like tweaking some LLVM options then forgotting to rebuild, causing headaches. So it's in their best interest to provide a safety net like this.\r\n\r\n## Potential improvements\r\n\r\n* Remove uninteresting options like the `build_args`; they might contain interesting things sometime in the future, we can add them back at any time.\r\n* Diff the expected and actual stamp content more thoroughly and tell the user exactly why they're getting LLVM rebuilt, i.e. which configuration changed, even possibly asking for confirmation. This could be done in a separate PR if deemed necessary; I myself don't see it very pressing.\r\n\r\nr? @alexcrichton ", "created_at": "2016-12-30T15:05:52Z", "updated_at": "2017-01-04T08:22:26Z", "closed_at": "2017-01-04T08:22:26Z", "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "337e488c2edbe81423f5d1c63c82490e3b092abc", "assignee": {"login": "alexcrichton", "id": 64996, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY0OTk2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/64996?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton", "html_url": "https://github.com/alexcrichton", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "assignees": [{"login": "alexcrichton", "id": 64996, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY0OTk2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/64996?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton", "html_url": "https://github.com/alexcrichton", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": 